-- Yahoo rises on CEO's Microsoft remarks
-- 
-- Wed May 28, 2008 7:36pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/28/us-markets-yahoo-idUSN2844866420080528

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Yahoo ( YHOO.O ) rose in extended-hours trading after Chief Executive Jerry Yang said Microsoft ( MSFT.O ) "has a lot of interest in buying the company and we are listening."  

 Yahoo shares rose 2.4 percent to $27.80 after the closing bell.